annotation.TEXT: -Something- Something! Dotted yellow block something filled yellow block something. Something!?
Not exactly an easy to hit multi-coin block...
So, we've got 4-4, 4-Ghost House, and 4-5 available right now.
Okay, that was glitchy. (Though that glitchiness probably saved my life!)
Oh, a hidden 1-up, that essentially gave that super koopa an extra life! (Because I missed with my tongue due to hitting it.)
Nope, but at least I didn't totally miss the goal tape!
Whoa, nearly got hit by that super koopa there...
Going back up...
I wonder if the gimmick will change in the second half of the level...
Well, wonder no more!
And, right from the get go, it's becoming tricky!
As usual, you guys get to vote on which one of these three levels I should start with next time!

1 vote for me to feed Yoshi enemies until his stomach becomes a super-massive black hole that swallows up the entire universe, thereby saving it from being destroyed by man, 1 vote for Perfect Cherry Blossom's Phantasm Stage, 1 vote for me to learn how to hack Wii games, 1 vote for Midway Moor ("Center Plain" with Luigifan22222's translation), and 3 votes for 3-1! (Whew! There were so many, I couldn't fit them all in one annotation!)
Okay, that was way too risky. Had I missed there, it would've been another Yoshi sacrifice!
See these coins? Remember that spot for later...
A blue koopa could be useful...
Just take everything nice and slowly, and there shouldn't be any trouble.
Well, screw that 1-up...
Also, I have to quickly learn that stepping on a saw hurts. At least I got my feather back right away.
And, it's boss time!
It's an autoscrolling level, with obvious restricted movement.
I saw a ledge down there...
The room's border is purple, so the hidden 1-up should be there.
I probably shouldn't take such risks just to check if pipes can be entered...
Much better!
Don't jump around crazily on these platforms, and you should be fine.
Welcome back to Super SIG World 21! I decided to check out this pyramid again, and I found a well-hidden something...
Oh, man. Eating Pokey is going to be a challenge in this weather.
Nuts. I was hoping for a feather there...
Push.
4-GH
So many super koopas... I'd better be careful, or I'll likely lose Yoshi.
Another P-switch, and it's quite obvious what it's used for.
Yep! Can I get 50 stars?
One...
And that's all five! Alright, I'm outta here!
Halfway done. I wonder what the second half's gimmick will be...
To be continued...
At least I've got a cape, but I don't want to abuse my flying ability too much...
Two...
However, I missed the Yoshi coin near the start, and apparently at least one other one, since I only got three. Hmm... Where would that other one be...?
Bingo! That's three...
Why does is seem like every time I get to a boss with fireballs, it's one of the bosses that's not affected by them?
Nuts. Missed the Yoshi coin. I'll make a return visit for it later. Right now, let's just avoid getting cut up!
I bet I can kill that guy...
Also, that pipe over there just takes you back to the level. (I checked it offscreen.)
And I once again failed to get a perfect. Nuts!
That was also kind of close. Imagine if I'd pressed the P-switch when the lava was in the wrong position!
Interesting music, and Lightgod87 has informed me that it's Bomberman GB - Area 5. Thanks!
A high number of the votes also wanted me to finish up world 5, so into the castle we go!
Four...
Hey, guys? I really don't think this is the best weather to be playing baseball in.
Whoa, that was close!
Looks like we've got Lemmy with an extra helping of podoboos!
Oh, man. Look at all the Phantos!
So, are we done?
Yep! Also, I forgot to speed up this part of the video. Oh, well.
And I bet I know where the other missing one is... If I get the lava here to start moving, then go back to the left...
Okay, with world 5 now complete, all that remains right now is world 4!
Now, let's wait patiently while occasionally jumping over the fire bar.
Yep. Did I get at least 30 coins?

First the silly votes: 1 vote for me to be Marisa and turn Yoshi into Rumia, 1 vote for me to go to 1-2 and warp to world -1, 1 vote for me to take the Epoch to world 19-99 AD, 1 vote for me to defeat Ryuuguu Komachi at the Fujisan Rock festival, 1 vote for Secret 6 in New SMW2: Yoshi's Island, 1 vote for me to push down Jack and Jill and steal their pail of water on the hill,
Time for yet another bonus game.
It's continuously pushing me to the right, but as long as it doesn't do anything unexpected, I should be able to deal with it.
Lava. Is it rising and falling lava? No? Hmm...
Oh, hey there red ! blocks! How's it going?
Something something something, something. Something, something something.
A P-switch. I wonder where I should use it?
Going down...
Whoa, we've got a sandstorm going on here!
Stupid Maverick Thwomp...
Ooh, anything good in there?
Oh, what's this? There's a door where those coins used to be! I thought those coins seemed suspicious...

Now, the serious votes: 2 votes for 4-5, 3 votes for 4-GH, and 8 votes for 5-3 (including 5 votes for me to finish up world 5). Oh, and the yellow switch exit from the pyramid just happened to place me on 5-3, so I don't even have to move from this spot!
Alright, so let's take a look at the voting results for the next level I'll be playing...
If the above annotations don't look nice and organized, I blame YouTube. For me, they sometimes don't appear quite the way I've made them in the annotation editor...
Ah, there it goes. I guess here's where the rising and falling lava gimmick really begins.
Meh. I don't want to take forever here. Let's just move on.
Yep, it's now pushing me to the left, so I'll be fighting it the whole way here.
Oh, man. Look at that yellow switch!
Too bad this isn't Paper Mario, where you can deal double-digit damage to Dry Bones with fire attacks!
Alright, that unlocks another warp star that takes us back to Midway Moor no doubt, but let's go back into the castle and get all the Yoshi coins...
This castle needs to be scrubbed.
Well, that's done and over with.
So, with this, I have now hit all four switches! Awesome!
Yep, that worked! I'm glad I didn't encounter a fireball as I did that!
